22 regarding the results of an Indiana account holder's age estimation
23 under subsection (c)(2) not later than thirty (30) days after the date
24 on which the Indiana account holder completes the age estimation
25 process.
26 (h) A social media provider that receives verifiable parental
27 consent for the continuation of an account under this section shall
28 provide the parent or legal guardian with the option to receive a
29 separate password for the account as described under
30 IC 24-16-3-2(d).
31 Chapter 5. Use and Retention of Information
32 Sec. 1. A social media provider that receives information from
33 an individual for the purpose of the individual's provision of
34 verifiable parental consent to the social media provider:
35 (1) may not use the information for any purpose other than
36 registering the individual's provision of verifiable parental
37 consent; and
38 (2) shall, except as necessary to comply with any other
39 applicable state or federal law or regulation, delete the
40 information immediately after registering the individual's
41 provision of verifiable parental consent.
42 Chapter 6. Enforcement
